Job Description:
JOB DESCRIPTION: Electric Power Systems (EPS) is an innovative Technology company that supplies Energy Storage Systems to Aerospace & Transportation applications. Our Engineering team develops innovative cutting-edge system solutions to address major societal issues by providing sustainable electric propulsion systems. EPS is seeking talent for our new state-of-the art facility located in beautiful North Logan, UT, who is drawn to solving new problems, comfortable with thinking out of the box, has a proven history of successful innovation, and enjoys working on a team with like-minded individuals.
POSTION SUMMARY:
ROLES AND RESPONSIBILITES
 Serve as a senior subject matter expert and direct the planning, design, and modification of individual software engineering projects;
 Develop and implement innovative solutions to optimize processes;
 Develop and provide technical support to developer teams around battery management software;
 Develop software requirements and software architectures;
 Generate and validate software code;
 Support documentation and validation toward FAA certification;
 Use source debuggers and visual development environments;
 Translate business requirements into technical specifications to help manage project priorities and timelines;
 Write, modify, and debug software for client applications;
 Provide analytical support and direction for the Software Engineering team, and mentor junior members;
 Test and document software for client applications;
 Analyze existing software to strategize about upgrades, features, or new platforms.
COMPETENCIES
 Creative and competent in designing and integrating software code to optimize battery performance;
 Excellent interpersonal and technical communication skills;
 Strong understanding of industry standards, contracts, and protocols;
 Inspect completed software projects to ensure conformance with design standards;
 Supervise and train project staff as needed;
 Design, maintain, implement, and improve software code to meet project scope;
 Code fixes for bugs and software defects;
 C and its use in real-time, safety-critical embedded systems;
 Details of the ARM Cortex-M architecture and its use in bare metal environments;
 On-chip and external peripheral driver development, and the effective use of interrupts, polling, and DMA in firmware designs;
 Bus protocols such as CAN, A429, SPI, I2C and Ethernet;
 Software unit test and integration test development, and the design of software for testability and introspection;
 Use of development tools such as debuggers, oscilloscopes, and logic analyzers;
 Examination of component data sheets and hardware schematics;
 Analyze requirements and create software designs;
QUALIFICATIONS AND EDUCATION REQUIREMENTS
 Bachelor’s in computer engineering; Master’s Degree preferred;
 3-5 years of engineering experience;
 10-15 years in safety critical software development;
 Operation in a DO-178C environment;
 Involvement in certification of critical software using DO178C and DO254;
 Development of software for fault-tolerant/redundant embedded systems;
 Development of automation tools with Python;
 Use of continuous integration pipelines and software deployment systems;
 Configuration of compiler toolchains and build systems;
 Development of software in a command-line oriented Linux environment;
 Strong understanding of industry standards, contracts, and protocols;
 Understanding of fundamental electrical engineering principles and batteries;
 Strong understanding of automotive drivelines and vehicle architectures;
 Technical capacity in terms of designing battery cells, BMS and other required components.
SPECIAL REQUIREMENTS
 This position requires a government security clearance;
 You must be a US Citizen for consideration.
